<h2>FAQs</h2>

<div class="faq">
    <h3>1. Are there gluten-free options at Universal Studios Hollywood?</h3>
    <p>Yes, Universal Studios Hollywood offers a variety of gluten-free options across its restaurants, snack stands, and food carts. Be sure to inform the staff of your dietary needs to ensure your meal is safe.</p>

    <h3>2. Can I find gluten-free snacks at the park?</h3>
    <p>Absolutely! The park offers gluten-free snacks such as popcorn, fruit cups, and gluten-free cookies. Always check with the staff to avoid cross-contamination.</p>

    <h3>3. Is Butterbeer gluten-free?</h3>
    <p>Yes, Butterbeer is gluten-free and a must-try for any Harry Potter fan visiting The Wizarding World of Harry Potter.</p>

    <h3>4. How can I avoid cross-contamination?</h3>
    <p>To avoid cross-contamination, always inform the staff of your dietary needs and ask about their preparation methods. It’s also a good idea to bring your own snacks as a backup.</p>
</div>

<h2>Conclusion</h2>

<p>Universal Studios Hollywood has made great strides in accommodating gluten-free diets, offering a variety of delicious and safe options across the park. From hearty meals at The Three Broomsticks to gluten-free snacks at various stands, there’s something for everyone. By planning ahead and communicating with the staff, you can enjoy a worry-free dining experience while exploring the magic of Universal Studios Hollywood. So pack your bags, grab your wand, and get ready for an unforgettable adventure—gluten-free style!</p>

